  6  Hausdorff completions of uniform spaces.
  7  
  8  The goal is to construct a left-adjoint to the inclusion of complete Hausdorff uniform spaces
  9  into all uniform spaces. Any uniform space `α` gets a completion `completion α` and a morphism
 10  (ie. uniformly continuous map) `completion : α → completion α` which solves the universal
 11  mapping problem of factorizing morphisms from `α` to any complete Hausdorff uniform space `β`.
 12  It means any uniformly continuous `f : α → β` gives rise to a unique morphism
 13  `completion.extension f : completion α → β` such that `f = completion.extension f ∘ completion α`.
 14  Actually `completion.extension f` is defined for all maps from `α` to `β` but it has the desired
 15  properties only if `f` is uniformly continuous.
 16  
 17  Beware that `completion α` is not injective if `α` is not Hausdorff. But its image is always
 18  dense. The adjoint functor acting on morphisms is then constructed by the usual abstract nonsense.
 19  For every uniform spaces `α` and `β`, it turns `f : α → β` into a morphism
 20    `completion.map f : completion α → completion β`
 21  such that
 22    `coe ∘ f = (completion.map f) ∘ coe`
 23  provided `f` is uniformly continuous. This construction is compatible with composition.
 24  
 25  In this file we introduce the following concepts:
 26  
 27  * `Cauchy α` the uniform completion of the uniform space `α` (using Cauchy filters). These are not
 28    minimal filters.
 29  
 30  * `completion α := quotient (separation_setoid (Cauchy α))` the Hausdorff completion.
 31  
 32  This formalization is mostly based on
 33    N. Bourbaki: General Topology
 34    I. M. James: Topologies and Uniformities
 35  From a slightly different perspective in order to reuse material in topology.uniform_space.basic.
 36  -/

 46  /-- Space of Cauchy filters
 47  
 48  This is essentially the completion of a uniform space. The embeddings are the neighbourhood filters.
 49  This space is not minimal, the separated uniform space (i.e. quotiented on the intersection of all
 50  entourages) is necessary for this.
 51  -/
